==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Earn
<hw>Earn</hw> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rn)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Earned</conjf> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rnd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Earning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS.
<ets>earnian</ets>; akin to OHG. <ets>arn⟦omac⟧n</ets> to reap,
<ets>aran</ets> harvest, G. <ets>ernte</ets>, Goth. <ets>asans</ets>
harvest, <ets>asneis</ets> hireling, AS. <ets>esne</ets>; cf. Icel.
<ets>⟦oum⟧nn</ets> working season, work.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
merit or deserve, as by labor or service; to do that which entitles one
to (a reward, whether the reward is received or not).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The high repute⟦br⟧
Which he through hazard huge must <qex>earn</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To acquire by labor, service, or performance; to
deserve and receive as compensation or wages; <as>as, to <ex>earn</ex> a
good living; to <ex>earn</ex> honors or laurels.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>earn</qex> that [what] I eat.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The bread I have <qex>earned</qex> by the hazard of my life or the
sweat of my brow.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Earned run</b></col> <fld>(Baseball)</fld>, <cd>a run
which is made without the assistance of errors on the opposing
side.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Obtain</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Earn</ent>⟦br⟧

